Building Density: The total count of buildings within a specific radius (e.g., 500 meters) of the sample point.Building Coverage Ratio (BCR): The percentage of land area covered by building structures inside that radius ($BCR = \frac{\text{Building Area}}{\text{Total Buffer Area}} \times 100$).Road Density: The total linear length (in meters) of all roads within the radius divided by the buffer area.Distance to Nearest Road: The exact distance from the sample point to the closest street line string.
Run this script in your local environment. It reads the Merged_ML_Dataset.csv you generated from GEE, cross-references it with your OSM GeoJSON files, and appends the new morphology columns.

